            comes from regressing the level of new product introductions on monthly dummies for the individual industries in the sample. It appears that just the seasons are responsible for roughly 9.2% (Instruments) to about 17.1% (Transportation Equipment) of the variability of new product introductions. The rest of the variability is due to other factors such as market demand.

In the present section, I test formally the relation between the seasonal patterns of new product introductions and the industry and aggregate demand (hypothesis 1).13For that, the log level of new product introductions is regressed on proxies of market and aggregate demand. Specifically, the log growth rates of industrial production
